name: IndexSet.Index
desc: The mechanism for accessing the integers stored in an IndexSet.

items.name: static func != (IndexSet.Index, IndexSet.Index) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two values are not equal.

items.name: static func ..< (IndexSet.Index) -> PartialRangeUpTo<IndexSet.Index>
items.desc: Returns a partial range up to, but not including, its upper bound.

items.name: static func < (IndexSet.Index, IndexSet.Index) -> Bool
items.desc: Indicates that one index is less than another.

items.name: static func == (IndexSet.Index, IndexSet.Index) -> Bool
items.desc: Indicates that two indexes are equal.

items.name: var description: String
items.desc: A textual description of the index.

items.name: static func ... (IndexSet.Index) -> PartialRangeFrom<IndexSet.Index>
items.desc: Returns a partial range extending upward from a lower bound.

items.name: static func ... (IndexSet.Index) -> PartialRangeThrough<IndexSet.Index>
items.desc: Returns a partial range up to, and including, its upper bound.

items.name: static func ... (IndexSet.Index, IndexSet.Index) -> ClosedRange<IndexSet.Index>
items.desc: Returns a closed range that contains both of its bounds.

items.name: static func ..< (IndexSet.Index, IndexSet.Index) -> Range<IndexSet.Index>
items.desc: Returns a half-open range that contains its lower bound but not its upper bound.
